        },
        "collapsible_tab_PAyNwP": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "BassFlow Vent Pressure System",
            "content": "<p>The front acoustic chamber of the isobaric bass drivers integrates a dedicated BassFlow Vent Pressure System, designed to balance pneumatic pressure in the ear canal and regulate airflow to the dynamic woofers. This innovative system prevents pressure buildup for comfortable extended listening while enabling precise control over bass texture and response. By managing airflow, the system fine-tunes woofer performance, enhancing resonance and damping properties for powerful, detailed bass. Quantitative control ensures balanced bass intensity without overpowering mids and highs, while qualitative adjustments refine warmth, clarity, and punch, delivering a satisfying and cohesive sound signature.</p>"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_n38dzJ": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Dual Isobaric Dynamic Woofer",
            "content": "<p>The Z06's 6mm dual isobaric woofer is designed for exceptional bass performance while maintaining overall audio balance. Featuring dual diaphragms and high-strength neodymium magnets, it delivers powerful and precise sound with minimal distortion. The isobaric configuration, where two drivers work in tandem, reduces Total Harmonic Distortion (THD) and enables deeper, cleaner bass. Advanced acoustic filtering ensures the woofer operates within a specific frequency range, minimizing overlap with balanced armature drivers for accurate and detailed sound reproduction. High-strength magnets enhance efficiency and responsiveness, providing fast transient response and detailed bass nuances. Together, these innovations create a rich, immersive listening experience with powerful, well-balanced bass seamlessly integrated into the overall sound signature.</p>"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_HffCBq": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "3D Printed Enclosure and Precision Engineering",
            "content": "<p>The Z06 utilizes AAW's third-generation digital enclosure and acoustic chamber design, fully leveraging a digitized design process. Through extensive computer simulations, driver and nozzle placements are iterated hundreds of times to achieve optimal phasing, response, and acoustic performance. Once perfected, the design transitions to precision 3D printing, ensuring tight tolerances and exact replication of the prototype for consistent quality. This advanced manufacturing process enhances structural integrity and guarantees performance uniformity across production. Rigorous quality checks further uphold AAW’s high standards, resulting in a hybrid in-ear monitor that delivers lush, vibrant, and spacious audio performance tailored for audiophiles and professionals alike.</p>"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_XefaKL": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Accessories and Warranty",
            "content": "<p>48\" Null Audio Epsilon UPOCC Copper Detachable Cable<br/>AAW Carrying Case<br/>3 Pairs SpinFit Silicone Tip(S/M/L)*<br/>3 Pairs AAW Short Stem Foam Tips(S/M/L)*<br/>6 Pairs AAW Assorted Silicone Tips (S/M/LX2)*<br/>1 Year Limited Warranty</p><p></p><p>* For Universal Fit Only</p>"
          }
        },
